==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lockup
<hw>Lock"up`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <sn>1.</sn> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A place
where persons under arrest are temporarily locked up; a watchhouse; a
jail.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The act or state of temporary imprisonment in a
lockup{1}.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A malfunction in a machine having moving parts, such
that the moving part cannot move; a seizure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lock washer</ent>⟦br⟧
